1
00:00:22,580 --> 00:00:27,660
♪Don't be afraid of the long journey♪

2
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:34,740
♪Love will comfort your missing♪

3
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:38,620
♪All the wounds will scab over♪

4
00:00:38,740 --> 00:00:41,980
♪And turn into the blossoms of time♪

5
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:48,700
♪Someone will wipe them away for you♪

6
00:00:49,300 --> 00:00:52,580
♪Don't feel lonely, moving on♪

7
00:00:52,940 --> 00:00:56,420
♪Share your story with time♪

8
00:00:56,460 --> 00:01:03,100
♪It will respond
with a gentle beam of light♪

9
00:01:03,220 --> 00:01:06,820
♪Wishing you find her in the crowd♪

10
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:10,220
♪And rest content with a simple life♪

11
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:16,660
♪Even though life is full of regrets♪

12
00:01:17,380 --> 00:01:20,180
♪May you always maintain enthusiasm♪

13
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:22,540
♪For every winter and summer♪

14
00:01:23,900 --> 00:01:25,980
[Love Is Panacea]
[Episode 19]

15
00:01:25,980 --> 00:01:26,960
[The show is the Major Project
for Supporting Literature and Art]

16
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:27,980
[in Sichuan Province in 2022]

17
00:01:27,980 --> 00:01:29,980
[Based on the novel "Healer"
by Ningmeng Yuyan]

18
00:01:30,020 --> 00:01:31,820
Dr. Li, are you done eating?

19
00:01:31,980 --> 00:01:33,140
If you are, I'll pay the bill.

20
00:01:38,180 --> 00:01:39,340
I'm clear on the framework

21
00:01:39,340 --> 00:01:40,500
and standard procedures.

22
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,940
If there's anything else,

23
00:01:42,460 --> 00:01:43,500
we can discuss it over email.

24
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:44,380
I'll get going now.

25
00:01:44,620 --> 00:01:46,700
Her body language shows

26
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:47,660
that she likes you.

27
00:01:47,660 --> 00:01:49,460
But at the same time she's rejecting you.

28
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:51,260
Since she has already rejected you,

29
00:01:51,260 --> 00:01:54,060
why don't you consider other people?

30
00:01:54,180 --> 00:01:54,980
Li Wantong,

31
00:01:55,660 --> 00:01:56,940
this is my final notice.

32
00:01:57,620 --> 00:01:59,340
We've already had a meal together.

33
00:01:59,580 --> 00:02:01,700
If there are any other work matters,

34
00:02:02,100 --> 00:02:03,740
please communicate via email.

35
00:02:03,860 --> 00:02:06,580
I will not accept your pursuit.

36
00:02:06,780 --> 00:02:09,300
Dr. Gu, pursuing you is my right.

37
00:02:09,300 --> 00:02:10,260
You can reject me,

38
00:02:10,260 --> 00:02:11,500
but I'll still pursue you.

39
00:02:19,060 --> 00:02:20,420
The bill, please.

40
00:02:21,020 --> 00:02:22,580
I will come to you again!

41
00:02:51,620 --> 00:02:52,580
(What exactly do you take everything)

42
00:02:52,580 --> 00:02:54,700
(that happened between us as?)

43
00:02:55,900 --> 00:02:58,260
(We went through so much in Lacaya.)

44
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:00,700
(Can we end it
just by saying it's over?)

45
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:02,420
(Can you wrap it up so hastily)

46
00:03:02,420 --> 00:03:04,180
(without giving me an explanation?)

47
00:03:04,180 --> 00:03:05,060
(The dream is over.)

48
00:03:06,980 --> 00:03:08,300
(So the story should end too.)

49
00:03:25,900 --> 00:03:26,780
(Su Wei'an,)

50
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:28,420
(is leaving you)

51
00:03:29,820 --> 00:03:31,660
(really the better choice for you?)

52
00:03:37,180 --> 00:03:37,980
Su Wei'an,

53
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:43,300
you finally got your wish.

54
00:03:50,620 --> 00:03:51,940
It's all over now.

55
00:04:09,380 --> 00:04:11,100
(Come to the hospital tomorrow)

56
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:13,060
(and bring tasty food.)

57
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:21,060
Dr. Lu!

58
00:04:24,780 --> 00:04:25,940
Are you eating randomly again?

59
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:31,420
What did you eat?

60
00:04:42,220 --> 00:04:44,540
Didn't the doctor tell you
not to eat spicy food?

61
00:04:50,060 --> 00:04:51,740
What did you bring me to eat?

62
00:04:52,460 --> 00:04:53,460
Rice Paste!

63
00:04:53,500 --> 00:04:54,860
That's all you can eat now.

64
00:04:55,660 --> 00:04:57,140
Sounds so plain.

65
00:04:58,060 --> 00:04:58,980
You're not sincere.

66
00:05:00,460 --> 00:05:01,860
[Patent Assignment Contract]
Then I'll

67
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:04,940
just keep this contract to myself.

68
00:05:16,420 --> 00:05:17,700
Did you agree?

69
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:29,380
[Amount of Assignment: one CNY]

70
00:05:30,980 --> 00:05:31,940
Is the assignment fee

71
00:05:33,180 --> 00:05:34,140
only one yuan?

72
00:05:34,380 --> 00:05:35,740
Don't get too excited.

73
00:05:37,020 --> 00:05:39,140
My contract states very clearly

74
00:05:39,660 --> 00:05:42,380
that unless you can resolve

75
00:05:42,380 --> 00:05:44,020
the incomplete brain stem fiber issue,

76
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:46,020
you are not allowed

77
00:05:46,660 --> 00:05:48,420
to apply this patent

78
00:05:48,860 --> 00:05:50,260
clinically.

79
00:05:52,460 --> 00:05:53,700
To fix this defect,

80
00:05:54,220 --> 00:05:56,660
the funding and time
you'll need to invest later on

81
00:05:58,100 --> 00:05:59,180
will be considerable.

82
00:06:02,580 --> 00:06:04,220
I won't be around to see it anyway.

83
00:06:05,500 --> 00:06:06,300
So you

84
00:06:07,260 --> 00:06:08,380
figure it out yourselves.

85
00:06:09,380 --> 00:06:10,180
Rest assured.

86
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:12,380
Jiehui will definitely do its best.

87
00:06:12,780 --> 00:06:14,060
We will work hard

88
00:06:14,460 --> 00:06:16,180
not to let your lifelong research
go to waste.

89
00:06:17,180 --> 00:06:18,340
Don't break your promise.

90
00:06:19,660 --> 00:06:20,460
I won't.

91
00:06:22,260 --> 00:06:23,420
Come here, little girl.

92
00:06:24,340 --> 00:06:25,500
Let's take a photo together.

93
00:06:27,260 --> 00:06:28,620
You, this young girl,

94
00:06:29,460 --> 00:06:31,220
are very likable.

95
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:34,180
Here!

96
00:06:35,180 --> 00:06:37,500
Three, two, one!

97
00:06:39,660 --> 00:06:40,580
Let me check.

98
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:46,220
Come on! Why the long face?

99
00:06:48,860 --> 00:06:49,860
I've lived

100
00:06:51,420 --> 00:06:52,700
a good life.

101
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:57,060
My biggest regret

102
00:06:58,660 --> 00:07:00,180
is not completing the research project.

103
00:07:02,460 --> 00:07:03,660
But in returning to China this time,

104
00:07:05,860 --> 00:07:07,700
I found the right people
to hand over to.

105
00:07:11,220 --> 00:07:12,340
And you took me

106
00:07:12,780 --> 00:07:13,980
to so many places

107
00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:15,300
and took so many photos for me.

108
00:07:17,260 --> 00:07:18,460
My final memories

109
00:07:19,460 --> 00:07:20,700
are beautiful ones.

110
00:07:25,060 --> 00:07:26,220
I have no worries

111
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:29,940
for my final days.

112
00:07:34,460 --> 00:07:35,260
Wei'an,

113
00:07:37,460 --> 00:07:38,380
thank you.

114
00:07:41,620 --> 00:07:43,340
Thank you, Dr. Lu.

115
00:07:45,460 --> 00:07:46,700
Don't cry anymore. Come here.

116
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:47,740
Let's take another one!

117
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,980
[Shen'gang City]

118
00:07:55,980 --> 00:07:56,780
Thanks.

119
00:07:58,420 --> 00:07:59,220
Hi!

120
00:08:01,380 --> 00:08:02,500
It's you again.

121
00:08:03,380 --> 00:08:05,220
Why did you follow me to Shen'gang City?
I'm having a conference here.

122
00:08:05,220 --> 00:08:06,620
I'm here to study

123
00:08:06,660 --> 00:08:09,940
and look for an opportunity
to collaborate across disciplines.

124
00:08:10,660 --> 00:08:12,300
How did you know the hotel
I'm staying at?

125
00:08:12,300 --> 00:08:13,260
I don't.

126
00:08:13,260 --> 00:08:14,580
The hospital booked this hotel
for everyone.

127
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:16,140
I just reminded them

128
00:08:16,140 --> 00:08:18,620
that they can book a few rooms together
so that they get a discount.

129
00:08:19,620 --> 00:08:22,460
That means
we're destined for each other.

130
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:23,780
And we share common interests

131
00:08:23,780 --> 00:08:25,220
and career paths.

132
00:08:25,580 --> 00:08:27,060
So Dr. Gu, don't you think

133
00:08:27,060 --> 00:08:29,100
we should try to make this work?

134
00:08:30,060 --> 00:08:31,300
There's no "we".

135
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:33,540
I don't want to be included.

136
00:08:54,980 --> 00:08:57,900
This is my period cycle chart.

137
00:08:57,900 --> 00:09:00,460
If you are unable
to fall in love with me

138
00:09:00,460 --> 00:09:01,540
and marry me in the short term,

139
00:09:01,580 --> 00:09:04,260
and then naturally have a child,

140
00:09:04,260 --> 00:09:04,900
that's okay.

141
00:09:04,900 --> 00:09:07,900
We can skip over these mundane steps.

142
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:10,500
We should directly create a child
with excellent genes.

143
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,900
Create a child?

144
00:09:14,060 --> 00:09:14,860
True,

145
00:09:14,860 --> 00:09:16,100
ordinary people may not be able to

146
00:09:16,100 --> 00:09:17,340
accept this idea.

147
00:09:17,340 --> 00:09:19,980
But Dr. Gu, you and I are both doctors.

148
00:09:20,220 --> 00:09:21,660
We understand clearly in our hearts

149
00:09:21,660 --> 00:09:23,340
that all species are the same.

150
00:09:23,340 --> 00:09:25,340
Only excellent genes
should be passed down.

151
00:09:25,340 --> 00:09:26,100
As for love,

152
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:28,220
it's just a fig leaf humans invented

153
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:30,500
for the sake of reproducing offspring.

154
00:09:31,940 --> 00:09:32,660
So do you believe

155
00:09:32,660 --> 00:09:34,460
humans and animals are no different?

156
00:09:34,860 --> 00:09:38,060
Mating and reproduction are instinctive?

157
00:09:38,340 --> 00:09:39,500
Of course not.

158
00:09:39,860 --> 00:09:41,690
Animal instincts are random.

159
00:09:41,740 --> 00:09:42,650
But you are my

160
00:09:42,650 --> 00:09:44,620
carefully selected target.

161
00:09:44,690 --> 00:09:47,060
What meaning is there in reproducing

162
00:09:47,300 --> 00:09:48,410
without emotion and love?

163
00:09:48,460 --> 00:09:49,780
How can you say there's no love?

164
00:09:50,220 --> 00:09:51,260
I have love!

165
00:09:51,580 --> 00:09:54,860
Listen, some people love money,
some love lust.

166
00:09:55,020 --> 00:09:57,340
And I just happen to
love your genes very much.

167
00:09:57,340 --> 00:09:57,930
Therefore,

168
00:09:57,930 --> 00:09:59,260
our two excellent genes

169
00:09:59,260 --> 00:10:00,380
should combine.

170
00:10:00,460 --> 00:10:02,780
Otherwise, it would be a crime
against human evolution.

171
00:10:05,780 --> 00:10:06,940
Li Wantong,

172
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:09,020
I can't listen to another word you say.

173
00:10:09,020 --> 00:10:10,260
Let me tell you once again:

174
00:10:10,540 --> 00:10:12,660
there is no possibility
between you and me.

175
00:10:13,940 --> 00:10:15,300
I'm done eating, goodbye.

176
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:21,260
Table No. 3 is paying.

177
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:25,940
Eliot,

178
00:10:27,340 --> 00:10:28,460
what are you doing here?

179
00:10:29,460 --> 00:10:30,580
I'm here for the conference.

180
00:10:32,540 --> 00:10:33,500
Where is Su Wei'an?

181
00:10:36,860 --> 00:10:37,660
She...

182
00:10:39,700 --> 00:10:40,940
Our study shows

183
00:10:40,940 --> 00:10:44,220
that the activation of the bone
morphogenetic protein signaling pathway

184
00:10:44,220 --> 00:10:47,500
drives a subset
of diffuse intrinsic pontine glioma

185
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:49,180
to exit the stem cell state,

186
00:10:49,380 --> 00:10:50,980
promotes cell differentiation,

187
00:10:51,060 --> 00:10:54,300
as well as induces cell cycle arrest
and apoptosis.

188
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:04,020
Now let's take a look at
several sets of comparative images.

189
00:11:04,020 --> 00:11:05,580
Such perfect genes.

190
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:07,620
What a waste.

191
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:10,580
Do you know him?

192
00:11:14,420 --> 00:11:15,460
Who are you?

193
00:11:15,660 --> 00:11:18,060
I work in the Neurosurgery Department
at Sacre Coeur Hospital of UPMC.

194
00:11:18,060 --> 00:11:18,900
My name is Eliot.

195
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:22,340
In the Heatmap of Gene Expression...

196
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:25,300
I work in the Psychological Department
at Huaren Hospital. I'm Li Wantong.

197
00:11:26,620 --> 00:11:28,220
At a specific time point,

198
00:11:28,460 --> 00:11:31,140
show contrasting
gene expression patterns

199
00:11:31,140 --> 00:11:33,060
compared to the other Heatmap.

200
00:11:33,460 --> 00:11:34,300
If you look here,

201
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:36,300
you can tell the difference
between them.

202
00:11:52,900 --> 00:11:53,700
Eliot.

203
00:11:57,860 --> 00:11:59,180
Long time no see, Dr. Gu.

204
00:12:00,660 --> 00:12:01,660
That was a great speech.

205
00:12:03,060 --> 00:12:03,780
It seems I should engage in

206
00:12:03,780 --> 00:12:06,020
academic discussions with you
often in the future.

207
00:12:06,260 --> 00:12:07,460
Dr. Eliot, we welcome you

208
00:12:07,460 --> 00:12:08,860
to visit Jinhai City

209
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:10,860
and Huaren Hospital anytime
for exchange and collaboration.

210
00:12:11,780 --> 00:12:12,580
Dr. Gu,

211
00:12:13,740 --> 00:12:16,020
Lacaya is so memorable.

212
00:12:18,340 --> 00:12:19,660
Do you miss

213
00:12:19,660 --> 00:12:21,180
our days there very much?

214
00:12:23,660 --> 00:12:24,620
Unforgettable, indeed.

215
00:12:25,780 --> 00:12:28,060
I nearly accompanied
the General to his grave.

216
00:12:28,260 --> 00:12:30,700
And you almost took Su Wei'an back
to France.

217
00:12:30,700 --> 00:12:32,180
That's a beautiful misunderstanding.

218
00:12:33,660 --> 00:12:35,020
She only wanted to go to Paris

219
00:12:35,020 --> 00:12:37,140
to learn about
a new medical research project.

220
00:12:39,460 --> 00:12:40,260
What medical research?

221
00:12:46,420 --> 00:12:47,860
The Huntington's Disease.

222
00:12:49,700 --> 00:12:51,220
So she told you about it.

223
00:12:53,180 --> 00:12:54,740
Are you two dating now?

224
00:12:59,220 --> 00:13:01,780
Su Wei'an was ready to go to Paris

225
00:13:02,260 --> 00:13:04,020
as soon as she heard me mention

226
00:13:04,020 --> 00:13:05,900
Dr. Marta restarting the chorea project.

227
00:13:06,500 --> 00:13:07,840
But the experiments failed.

228
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:10,060
I lied to her.

229
00:13:11,780 --> 00:13:12,700
She was devastated.

230
00:13:13,660 --> 00:13:16,060
She said it didn't matter where she was

231
00:13:17,060 --> 00:13:18,180
if there was no cure.

232
00:13:20,260 --> 00:13:23,060
Gu, she's lucky to have you.

233
00:13:29,820 --> 00:13:30,740
(Where's Eliot?)

234
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:32,860
Why did he leave you behind?

235
00:13:33,940 --> 00:13:35,220
What happened?

236
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:37,580
I suddenly don't want to go.

237
00:13:40,460 --> 00:13:41,540
I want to live too.

238
00:13:45,540 --> 00:13:47,540
(At that time, she didn't know
about her aunt's illness.)

239
00:13:48,660 --> 00:13:50,740
(Who was she researching
new treatment methods for?)

240
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:53,380
(Su Wei'an, was it for yourself?)

241
00:13:53,460 --> 00:13:54,980
Sorry, I need to make a phone call.

242
00:14:00,460 --> 00:14:02,660
Please book the soonest flight
to Jinhai City.

243
00:14:02,660 --> 00:14:03,300
Thanks.

244
00:14:05,980 --> 00:14:08,340
[Jinhai City]

245
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:09,560
[Ambulance]

246
00:14:10,020 --> 00:14:11,740
Auntie!

247
00:14:11,740 --> 00:14:12,580
Yuan!

248
00:14:15,320 --> 00:14:17,280
[ER (Rescue area\Gastric lavage)]

249
00:14:17,380 --> 00:14:18,140
Doctor.

250
00:14:18,460 --> 00:14:20,300
The patient had an aneurysm rupture

251
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:21,380
and surgery at Huaren two weeks ago.

252
00:14:21,460 --> 00:14:22,540
She was discharged five days ago.

253
00:14:22,660 --> 00:14:23,660
Now she is in a deep coma

254
00:14:23,660 --> 00:14:24,900
with a GCS score of 4.

255
00:14:24,900 --> 00:14:26,060
There may be new bleeding.

256
00:14:26,260 --> 00:14:27,460
Neck rigidity, four-finger breadth.

257
00:14:27,580 --> 00:14:28,780
Get a head CT scan immediately.

258
00:14:28,780 --> 00:14:29,660
Prepare an OR.

259
00:14:29,660 --> 00:14:30,860
Contact Dr. He Xiaoguang right away.

260
00:14:30,980 --> 00:14:31,780
Got it.

261
00:14:32,500 --> 00:14:33,420
Contact who?

262
00:14:33,460 --> 00:14:34,460
The attending doctor on duty today

263
00:14:34,460 --> 00:14:35,580
is Dr. He Xiaoguang.

264
00:14:35,580 --> 00:14:36,460
He has extensive clinical experience.

265
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:37,300
He will be the lead surgeon

266
00:14:37,300 --> 00:14:38,060
for this operation.

267
00:14:44,340 --> 00:14:48,460
[Department of Anesthesiology
& Operating Room]

268
00:14:52,930 --> 00:14:53,620
Gu Yunzheng...

269
00:15:00,100 --> 00:15:02,940
[Handsome Gu]

270
00:15:02,980 --> 00:15:03,620
Done.

271
00:15:06,060 --> 00:15:06,980
Handsome?

272
00:15:07,080 --> 00:15:08,340
[Handsome Gu]

273
00:15:11,420 --> 00:15:12,660
(Su Wei'an, why didn't you get)

274
00:15:12,660 --> 00:15:14,260
(his contact information in China?)

275
00:15:20,620 --> 00:15:22,540
[Handsome Gu]

276
00:15:44,300 --> 00:15:45,140
Hello?

277
00:15:47,100 --> 00:15:48,340
Hello, Gu Yunzheng.

278
00:15:51,300 --> 00:15:52,260
This is Su Wei'an.

279
00:15:52,900 --> 00:15:53,900
My aunt is in the OR

280
00:15:55,060 --> 00:15:56,700
at Huaren Hospital right now.

281
00:15:56,700 --> 00:15:58,220
Her aneurysm ruptured again.

282
00:15:59,260 --> 00:16:01,060
But the surgeon tonight is He Xiaoguang.

283
00:16:01,060 --> 00:16:02,940
I'm afraid my aunt won't make it out.

284
00:16:05,180 --> 00:16:06,300
Don't worry, I'm here.

285
00:16:06,620 --> 00:16:07,300
It will be fine.

286
00:16:07,300 --> 00:16:08,180
I'll be right there.

287
00:16:12,380 --> 00:16:17,860
[First-Aid, Chest Pain Center]
[Stroke Center, Trauma Center]

288
00:16:44,140 --> 00:16:47,240
♪That sweetness from long ago♪

289
00:16:47,260 --> 00:16:48,300
Wei'an,

290
00:16:48,580 --> 00:16:49,620
I'm here.

291
00:16:51,580 --> 00:16:53,980
♪Seems like a riddle♪

292
00:16:54,060 --> 00:16:58,820
♪That fate deliberately arranged for me♪

293
00:16:58,940 --> 00:17:02,060
♪Now when I occasionally think back
on it♪

294
00:17:02,660 --> 00:17:05,780
♪I can't describe what emotions arise♪

295
00:17:06,260 --> 00:17:09,380
♪Perhaps it's
that I understand too well♪

296
00:17:09,420 --> 00:17:17,700
♪Once loved, I don't want to be
forgotten again♪

297
00:17:18,700 --> 00:17:21,820
♪It's okay if you forget it♪

298
00:17:22,340 --> 00:17:25,460
♪It's you who gave me the courage♪

299
00:17:26,220 --> 00:17:29,780
♪To enjoy the scenery
I will never reach♪

300
00:17:29,820 --> 00:17:33,380
♪I'll bless you♪

301
00:17:33,540 --> 00:17:36,700
♪It's okay if you forget it♪

302
00:17:37,220 --> 00:17:40,340
♪It's me who saved myself♪

303
00:17:40,460 --> 00:17:43,780
♪I've always loved you♪

304
00:17:43,900 --> 00:17:47,420
♪And never gaven up♪

305
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:55,120
Mom,

306
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,000
we can't give HDQ39

307
00:17:58,680 --> 00:17:59,880
to my aunt anymore.

308
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:02,480
Why?

309
00:18:03,680 --> 00:18:05,240
Her rebleeding aneurysm

310
00:18:08,040 --> 00:18:10,200
was very likely caused by this drug.

311
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:14,880
How did you know that?

312
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:17,840
Dr. Gu warned me before.

313
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:21,840
But at the time,

314
00:18:22,880 --> 00:18:24,400
I thought if it was just speculation,

315
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,680
we shouldn't stop
the medication arbitrarily.

316
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:29,360
If I hadn't told my aunt

317
00:18:29,360 --> 00:18:30,480
about the drug trial,

318
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:33,240
if I hadn't strongly recommended
she try the drug,

319
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:35,520
she wouldn't have had
a rebleeding aneurysm

320
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:36,840
in such a short time

321
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:39,880
and wouldn't be fighting
for her life in there now.

322
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,680
It's all my fault for harming her.

323
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,600
Silly girl,

324
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:49,320
when she tried the drug,

325
00:18:49,360 --> 00:18:51,200
it was a decision we all discussed
and agreed on together.

326
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:51,960
Am I right?

327
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:57,360
I was delusional,

328
00:18:58,680 --> 00:19:00,080
thinking I could help her.

329
00:19:01,720 --> 00:19:03,320
But instead I got her into trouble.

330
00:19:03,840 --> 00:19:04,960
No,

331
00:19:06,040 --> 00:19:07,520
You've done all this for her sake.

332
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:09,720
How could you have known
these things would happen?

333
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:10,600
Right?

334
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:14,160
You can't blame yourself for this.

335
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:17,200
Alright,
let's not think about it anymore.

336
00:19:19,400 --> 00:19:20,440
OK?

337
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:25,660
[Outpatient]

338
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:28,200
Pay attention
to her diet and daily life.

339
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:31,440
This patient likes to eat spicy food,

340
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,600
so you need to advise her
to avoid irritating foods.

341
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:33,960
Okay.

342
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:35,560
Nothing else, you can go now.

343
00:19:56,040 --> 00:19:58,360
You must have been exhausted these days.

344
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:00,240
No.

345
00:20:04,360 --> 00:20:05,280
Look at you.

346
00:20:06,920 --> 00:20:08,640
You must have been through
a lot of scares and fears.

347
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:09,800
You've been busy taking care of her
for a while.

348
00:20:10,560 --> 00:20:11,520
I'm fine.

349
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:13,840
It's just my aunt suffered a lot.

350
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:15,880
How is she now?

351
00:20:15,960 --> 00:20:16,880
Much better.

352
00:20:17,360 --> 00:20:20,160
She's been transferred to another ward
for continued observation.

353
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:21,680
Good.

354
00:20:23,880 --> 00:20:24,680
Why...

355
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,880
Why did you keep

356
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:30,960
my number in Lacaya?

357
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,000
In case Lacaya's doctors

358
00:20:39,040 --> 00:20:40,280
need remote assistance.

359
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:46,520
Just kidding, silly.

360
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:49,040
I'm afraid you won't be able to find me.

361
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:58,080
Actually these last few days,

362
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:02,960
I've been looking for a chance
to apologize to you.

363
00:21:04,280 --> 00:21:05,080
I'm sorry.

364
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:07,480
I feel your suspicion about HDQ39

365
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:08,480
may have been right.

366
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:10,720
If I had listened to you back then,

367
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:13,160
even if it was just suspicion,

368
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:16,240
and asked my aunt
to stop taking the medicine temporarily,

369
00:21:17,200 --> 00:21:18,400
things might not have turned out

370
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:20,080
the way they are now.

371
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:25,080
Right,

372
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:28,560
can I ask you a favor?

373
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,960
Can you help investigate

374
00:21:32,520 --> 00:21:33,890
whether HDQ39

375
00:21:35,320 --> 00:21:37,120
really induces aneurysms?

376
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:39,800
Su Wei'an,

377
00:21:41,680 --> 00:21:43,160
why don't you look into it yourself?

378
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:46,840
I'm...

379
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:49,080
You're also a medical student.

380
00:21:49,320 --> 00:21:50,800
Anything I can do,

381
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:52,360
you can do as well.

382
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:53,920
I'm just an undergraduate.

383
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:54,600
I can't.

384
00:21:54,600 --> 00:21:55,720
You haven't even tried.

385
00:21:55,720 --> 00:21:57,280
How do you know?

386
00:21:57,840 --> 00:21:59,440
Professor Lu also said

387
00:21:59,560 --> 00:22:02,160
you have excellent
medical talents and gifts.

388
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:03,680
Why do you want to waste them?

389
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:05,680
I really can't do it.

390
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:11,640
You are more likely than me
to uncover the truth.

391
00:22:12,320 --> 00:22:13,360
You are Gu Yunzheng!

392
00:22:13,520 --> 00:22:14,560
But I'm not you.

393
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:17,480
Su Wei'an,

394
00:22:17,840 --> 00:22:18,800
only you can resolve

395
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:20,520
your inner obstacles.

396
00:22:27,320 --> 00:22:28,600
I don't have time.

397
00:22:28,720 --> 00:22:31,000
I still need to take care of
my mom and my aunt.

398
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,200
I still need to make money.

399
00:22:32,400 --> 00:22:33,960
I've got a lot to do.

400
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:40,800
No, Su Wei'an.

401
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:43,640
You are afraid.

402
00:22:44,560 --> 00:22:46,120
Back then in Lacaya,

403
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:48,520
didn't you already try recklessly

404
00:22:48,520 --> 00:22:50,160
to follow Eliot to France

405
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:51,840
to participate in
medical research experiments?

406
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:56,640
How did you know?

407
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:58,920
Why could you do it then, but not now?

408
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:01,480
Because...

409
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:04,280
Because I was stubborn
and got my aunt into trouble.

410
00:23:09,240 --> 00:23:11,600
Even if there is only
the slightest chance,

411
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:14,280
we should still try our best.

412
00:23:14,280 --> 00:23:16,680
It's every medical student's instinct.

413
00:23:21,160 --> 00:23:22,760
Su Wei'an,
you're not doing this for yourself.

414
00:23:26,760 --> 00:23:28,080
Participating in the drug trial

415
00:23:28,880 --> 00:23:30,680
was not just for my aunt's illness.

416
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:36,560
I also carry the chorea gene.

417
00:23:40,320 --> 00:23:43,480
That's why I'm extra hopeful
that the HDQ39 will go to the market.

418
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,800
I'm not trustworthy,

419
00:23:48,080 --> 00:23:49,920
and I don't deserve to
participate in medical research.

420
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:58,080
Su Wei'an, you're right.

421
00:23:58,080 --> 00:24:00,880
You were extremely selfish
and despicable.

422
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:03,240
You knew participating in the drug trial

423
00:24:03,240 --> 00:24:05,840
could potentially lead to
a serious aneurysm rupture.

424
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:08,080
But you still treated your aunt
like a guinea pig

425
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:09,760
and forced her to participate.

426
00:24:10,800 --> 00:24:11,600
Is that right?

427
00:24:33,840 --> 00:24:36,000
If you didn't do that,

428
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,640
then what exactly did you do wrong

429
00:24:39,640 --> 00:24:40,880
that you are
tormenting yourself like this?

430
00:24:41,480 --> 00:24:42,800
If it's not my fault,

431
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:45,080
then whose fault is it?

432
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:52,640
Every time I have the tiniest hope,

433
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:57,040
what I end up with is despair.

434
00:24:58,360 --> 00:25:01,040
Why does misfortune have to befall me?

435
00:25:01,560 --> 00:25:03,240
Such a rare disease
with low probability,

436
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:04,920
why did it strike my family

437
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:05,680
with precision

438
00:25:05,680 --> 00:25:07,400
like lightning?

439
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:10,120
Why do cursed people like us

440
00:25:10,120 --> 00:25:12,320
exist in this world?

441
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:40,960
Hello, Wei'an.

442
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:42,280
Yuncheng,

443
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:45,680
I decided not to go to Jiehui.

444
00:25:46,080 --> 00:25:48,320
Why? Does the salary not satisfy you?

445
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:50,400
Regarding my aunt's aneurysm rupture,

446
00:25:51,360 --> 00:25:53,600
I think Gu Yunzheng's speculation
may be right.

447
00:25:53,720 --> 00:25:55,480
It is very likely

448
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:56,720
related to HDQ39.

449
00:25:58,080 --> 00:25:59,400
As a patient's family member,

450
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:01,800
I should not have more
conflicts of interest with Jiehui.

451
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:03,880
It does not comply with regulations.

452
00:26:04,360 --> 00:26:05,160
Also,

453
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:07,880
I'd like to ask you to help confirm
whether the drug trial team

454
00:26:08,280 --> 00:26:09,800
has reported the relevant situation

455
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:11,680
to the Drug Trial Supervisory Department

456
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:12,960
and Ethics Committee.

457
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:16,080
They can decide if the drug trial
needs to be suspended

458
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:17,920
and whether the trial team

459
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:19,480
can conduct some research

460
00:26:19,520 --> 00:26:20,720
to clarify if HDQ39

461
00:26:20,720 --> 00:26:22,360
is related to aneurysm formation.

462
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:23,840
I see.

463
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:26,120
I respect your decision.

464
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:31,400
If you need any help from me later on,

465
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:32,640
just let me know.

466
00:26:33,040 --> 00:26:34,080
Thank you, Yuncheng.

467
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:12,480
[Li Wantong / Email]
(Dr. Gu, I have a new target now.)

468
00:27:12,680 --> 00:27:14,040
(I won't pester you anymore.)

469
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:16,600
(However, the collaboration
between our two departments)

470
00:27:16,600 --> 00:27:18,120
(will continue.)

471
00:27:18,790 --> 00:27:20,440
(I can see your love)

472
00:27:20,440 --> 00:27:23,120
(has put a lot of pressure
on Su Wei'an.)

473
00:27:23,680 --> 00:27:25,360
(So here's the friendly tip:)

474
00:27:25,880 --> 00:27:27,520
(doting on and giving your all)

475
00:27:27,520 --> 00:27:28,720
(to your partner)

476
00:27:29,160 --> 00:27:31,160
(won't make you treasured.)

477
00:27:31,680 --> 00:27:33,520
(When you stop being so pushy)

478
00:27:33,520 --> 00:27:36,600
(and act indifferent
towards her instead,)

479
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:38,600
(she'll be the one chasing you.)

480
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:39,960
(In psychology,)

481
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:41,680
(this is called the Veblen effect.)

482
00:27:42,160 --> 00:27:43,200
(Good luck!)

483
00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:47,320
(Wei'an,)

484
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:49,560
(if you refuse to let me get close,)

485
00:27:50,480 --> 00:27:51,760
(then I'll just keep
orbiting around you.)

486
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:04,280
Jiang Muying,

487
00:28:05,120 --> 00:28:06,560
about Su Wei'an's situation,

488
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,880
whatever you know, I know too.

489
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:10,160
I love her,

490
00:28:10,440 --> 00:28:12,120
no matter the circumstances.

491
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:14,880
From the moment I fell for her,

492
00:28:15,680 --> 00:28:17,520
I never thought of giving up.

493
00:28:18,640 --> 00:28:19,840
So,

494
00:28:19,840 --> 00:28:22,360
as long as Su Wei'an does love me back.

495
00:28:22,960 --> 00:28:24,680
As long as
you really want what's best for her,

496
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:26,920
do as I say.

497
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:36,360
♪Rain falling on the deep blue sea♪

498
00:28:36,360 --> 00:28:40,600
♪Another tide, how many times♪

499
00:28:41,360 --> 00:28:45,640
♪Love, like a moth, risking it all♪

500
00:28:45,640 --> 00:28:46,780
[Income / Expense]

501
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:52,760
♪Searching for myself in the light♪

502
00:28:54,160 --> 00:28:55,640
♪In the long night♪

503
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:57,520
♪Mistaking the blazing flames♪

504
00:28:57,520 --> 00:28:59,800
♪For stars♪

505
00:28:59,800 --> 00:29:02,520
♪Too innocent
Only getting close an inch♪

506
00:29:02,520 --> 00:29:03,760
♪Burning into...♪

507
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:09,600
Mr. Wang.

508
00:29:09,600 --> 00:29:11,040
Hi, this is Su Wei'an.

509
00:29:12,880 --> 00:29:13,800
Um...

510
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:15,680
Please send me the schedule

511
00:29:15,680 --> 00:29:16,520
for the French conversation classes.

512
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:17,920
It's fine to schedule more classes.

513
00:29:19,040 --> 00:29:21,720
The price is what we agreed before,

514
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:23,960
400 yuan per class, right?

515
00:29:26,320 --> 00:29:27,560
Okay, thank you!

516
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:33,560
Stop that!

517
00:29:33,960 --> 00:29:36,120
Why aren't you going to

518
00:29:36,120 --> 00:29:37,440
the French translator job I recommended?

519
00:29:39,120 --> 00:29:40,120
One hundred thousand a month?

520
00:29:40,120 --> 00:29:41,400
There's no such good thing.

521
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:42,800
There must be a scam.

522
00:29:49,880 --> 00:29:51,080
Is the recruiter

523
00:29:51,560 --> 00:29:52,480
male or female?

524
00:29:53,680 --> 00:29:54,480
Male.

525
00:29:56,440 --> 00:29:57,480
What's wrong with a male?

526
00:29:58,280 --> 00:29:59,080
You...

527
00:29:59,240 --> 00:30:00,440
You are being sexist.

528
00:30:00,440 --> 00:30:01,560
You only translate for women?

529
00:30:03,680 --> 00:30:06,360
Free lunches don't exist.

530
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:13,280
Where are you going?

531
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:14,000
Bathroom.

532
00:30:15,360 --> 00:30:16,520
Hello, Dr. Gu.

533
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:18,800
Wei'an

534
00:30:20,320 --> 00:30:22,640
doesn't believe it's true whatsoever.

535
00:30:23,120 --> 00:30:25,280
Your idea doesn't seem to work.

536
00:30:30,760 --> 00:30:32,440
Should I really do that?

537
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,240
Yes.

538
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:38,680
Yes, okay.

539
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:55,120
Let me tell you the truth.

540
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:57,120
This job

541
00:30:58,040 --> 00:30:59,080
comes with conditions.

542
00:31:00,440 --> 00:31:01,960
See? What did I say?

543
00:31:05,080 --> 00:31:07,200
Come on.
Did you think I was going to harm you?

544
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:09,240
This is serious translation work.

545
00:31:09,800 --> 00:31:10,880
It's going to be published
in The Lancet.

546
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:14,600
The Lancet?

547
00:31:14,640 --> 00:31:15,160
Yeah.

548
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:19,040
That doesn't make sense.

549
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:22,120
If they can already publish
in such an authoritative journal,

550
00:31:22,720 --> 00:31:24,440
why would they need
to find another translator?

551
00:31:26,720 --> 00:31:29,800
Because the important task is urgent,
and the requirements are high.

552
00:31:30,080 --> 00:31:31,120
The content of this job

553
00:31:31,120 --> 00:31:32,800
is strictly confidential.

554
00:31:33,280 --> 00:31:35,320
Plus they need to interview first

555
00:31:35,360 --> 00:31:37,400
before they can hire someone.

556
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:38,640
That's why the pay is so high.

557
00:31:41,120 --> 00:31:42,720
I think making money is one thing.

558
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:45,360
But more importantly,
it's the opportunity

559
00:31:45,360 --> 00:31:46,240
to translate articles at this level.

560
00:31:46,760 --> 00:31:47,720
When is the interview?

561
00:31:47,720 --> 00:31:48,720
They said

562
00:31:48,920 --> 00:31:51,040
you must first sign
this non-disclosure agreement

563
00:31:51,120 --> 00:31:52,240
before they can arrange an interview.

564
00:31:57,720 --> 00:31:58,520
Alright.

565
00:32:00,280 --> 00:32:01,320
I'll take this job.

566
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:03,240
OK.

567
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:05,240
Where do I take it?

568
00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:19,020
[Huaren Medical University]
[Diligent, Adopt, Veracity]

569
00:32:35,360 --> 00:32:36,680
Hello, what's wrong?

570
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:39,320
Don't just stand at the gate. Go in!

571
00:32:39,320 --> 00:32:40,560
The interview is about to start.

572
00:32:43,320 --> 00:32:45,560
Jiang Muying, are you spying on me?

573
00:32:45,680 --> 00:32:47,440
I know you the best.

574
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:48,560
Su Wei'an.

575
00:32:48,560 --> 00:32:49,720
You only dropped out of school.

576
00:32:49,720 --> 00:32:51,080
It's not like you dropped out of life.

577
00:32:51,320 --> 00:32:52,920
Walk back in there
with your head held high.

578
00:32:53,520 --> 00:32:54,640
I'll be waiting for your good news!

579
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:56,240
Alright.

580
00:33:07,320 --> 00:33:08,920
The treatment of gliomas

581
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:10,640
is mainly surgical.

582
00:33:11,420 --> 00:33:14,340
However, due to
the infiltrative growth of the tumor

583
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:16,640
and the lack of clear boundaries
between brain tissues,

584
00:33:16,640 --> 00:33:18,440
it is difficult to resect it completely.

585
00:33:20,920 --> 00:33:22,760
(Jiang Muying, you are doomed!)

586
00:33:23,640 --> 00:33:25,320
That student who arrived right
before class was about to end!

587
00:33:26,600 --> 00:33:28,320
You'll answer my last question.

588
00:33:31,920 --> 00:33:33,000
Sorry, Sir.

589
00:33:33,080 --> 00:33:34,440
I'm not from your class.

590
00:33:34,600 --> 00:33:35,840
Miss Su Wei'an,

591
00:33:36,920 --> 00:33:37,920
I know you.

592
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:40,040
Your name is on the list.

593
00:33:40,480 --> 00:33:43,200
If you don't have the books,
you can borrow your classmate's.

594
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:45,480
If you can't answer the question,

595
00:33:45,680 --> 00:33:47,080
you can just say you don't know.

596
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:49,600
At most, this shows
your insufficient learning ability,

597
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:51,120
but deceiving the teacher

598
00:33:52,440 --> 00:33:54,040
shows your improper attitude.

599
00:33:57,040 --> 00:33:57,920
Alright, Sir.

600
00:33:58,240 --> 00:34:00,040
Please repeat your question.

601
00:34:00,040 --> 00:34:01,400
In what way do

602
00:34:01,400 --> 00:34:02,920
mutations in IDH occur?

603
00:34:02,920 --> 00:34:04,120
In most cases,

604
00:34:04,120 --> 00:34:05,400
